    "subject": "乘AI东风的内存制造商SK Hynix在美",
    "predicate": "ipo_listing",
    "object": "South Korean memory chipmaker SK Hynix, rival to Samsung and U.S.-based Micron , is planning to sell nearly 17.8 million shares in a U.S. IPO, the company said on Monday . Should its shares sell well (and there’s indication that they will), the company could raise around $28 billion, based on SK Hynix’s closing share price last Friday in Seoul, Bloomberg reports .",
    "claim_ref": "CL-724a5e04ebc0389a",
    "source_refs": [
